                <div class="column">
                    <h1 class="title is-spaced is-size-1-desktop is-size-2-tablet is-size3-mobile has-text-grey-darker">PIVOT</h1>
                    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-narrow-left has-text-grey-darker">The initial premise of this app was for an individual to define a goal or an item they'd like to receive as a gift for their birthday. However our User Interviews concluded that users are not willing to donate to a self-promoting campaign.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-narrow-left has-text-grey-darker">While the User Interviews did validate that some users would donate to a campaign that donated a portion to a charity, the results were not consistent and the use cases for an app of this nature is already available on the market.</p>
                    <br>
                    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-narrow-left has-text-grey-darker">The pain points that were identified by multiple users is a frustration with campaigns not doing a good job being transparent with the backers about project delivery time lines, or project status. Thus I've pivoted my capstone project and detailed the validation solution <a href="/ganttrack-case-study">here</a>.</p>
                </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="hero has-text-centered">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="column">
            <h1 class="title is-spaced is-size-1-desktop is-size-2-tablet is-size3-mobile has-text-grey-darker">USER PERSONAS</h1>
            <p class="subtitle is-6 is-narrow-left has-text-grey-darker">I created a User Persona based on my research and user interviews of those that experience the frustrations of a lack of transparency from crowdfunding campaigns. You can see the details of the Persona <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/10ciIPUU5KtjN0ZhpHoByLCPPhhZy_vn3PRn0OV0uSBM/edit" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
            <br>
            <p class="subtitle is-6 is-narrow-left has-text-grey-darker">Rather than running forward with building a prototype to gather additional market validation, I decided that quickest/least expensive way to do this would be to survey actual users that have experienced this pain-point.</p>
            <br>
            <p class="subtitle is-6 is-narrow-left has-text-grey-darker">In order to do this, I needed to leverage a colleagues campaign to get access to the users. I explained the value of the survey and that they would receive the shared data. They agreed and posted my survey on their next update. See the results below:</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="has-text-centered">
